reviewText:
A great game with the best FPS multiplayer I have ever played.
Its pros are:
A great multiplayer;
A very good story for the single player mode;
A few, but well defined classes for the multiplayer;
A good sort of weapons -again- for the multiplayer;
Good graphics.
The cons are:
The single player campaign is just too short;
Thare isn't a good variety of enemy skins in the single player;
Sometimes, in the single player campaign, you may find a few aleatory bugs;
The Express 870 Shotgun" DLC

HomeFront, is an interesting game. The story and tight narrative really hold the action together almost like the quality FPS's from developer valve. Kaos Studios has done something that the choked sea of call of duty clones has sorely needed in the FPS market, originality. This game is dripping with atmosphere thanks to its well thought out and executed graphical design and the games excellent pacing. You never feel ovewhelmed, but you are always on your toes. This game is a winner for me, the downside is its short, but honestly what game is not now adays? Its about 5 hours long which may ♥♥♥♥ people off but the story is so well done and the game play is paced and designed so well that I can't believe people would turn this one down.

The multiplayer is excellent, and the single player is a very well crafted story to which I look forward to returning to in the next game of the series {hopefully}

This game deserves your dollars, its only 50 dollars. Buy it.
